node.text:
If you have been smoking cigars for a while then you may have come across cigars with cracks, lifted leaves and even punctures. Sometimes these imperfections can ruin your cigar smoking experience and some times making the cigar not smokeable. I’ve long used this product from @perfeccigarsolutions called the PerfecRepair cigar glue. A patent pending design that has adhesive qualities with fibers inside to help seal punctures, cracks and bridge your cigar back to health. If you have loose cigar bands, you can also dab a little under the band to keep it in place. Next time you have a cigar in bad shape, don’t throw it away, try the PerfecRepair!
.
.
.
.
#cigaraccessories #cigarglue #perfecrepair #cigardoctor #cigaraficionado #botl #sotl

node.text:
Since the Corona Virus 🦠 the whole world has had to stay home and pass the time resulting in many #bottlekills 🙁🥃 Last night the piggy 🐷 gang gave a proper send off to one of their own 😆 I was succumbed to peer pressure by my Fiji 🏔 💧 Brothers @byron__c @armandrinksss @whisky_globetrotter 
@slainte_ruben 
to let this bottle go as I gulped the last mouthful of this sweet juice 🥤 @whistlepigwhiskey Boss Hog Samurai Scientist, you will be missed. Thank you for all the great memories and shares. You were sweet, plum like with a fruity finish. The unique Umeshu cask was a risk, but worked perfect. I drammed you mostly after a great meal, sometimes with a cigar. You never disappointed and the samples I sent to friends brightened their lonely nights. Thank you piggy number 6, salute! 🥺😆
.
.
.
.
.
#whiskeyreview #whiskygram #ryewhiskey #rip #bosshog #whistlepigwhiskey #samuraiscientist #soldiersfarewell #weekendvibes

node.text:
The famed BBMF from the @arturofuentecigars line. Hype or the real deal? This cigar has been sought after by many and always sold out when it hits the shelves adding to its popularity. The shape itself is unique with its unmistakable top knot characteristics. At first glance, it’s a beautiful cigar added with the Opus X band, it’s a work of art. Retailing anywhere from 60 - 100 dollars a stick, this is not a everyday smoke due to the price and limited availability. My experience with these vitolas are to light a little
More than just the end tip, at first puff it was sweet to the lips with a bit of toasty notes from the early char. The draw was large and full, blowing huge clouds of smoke. At the first third, this stick had a very sweet flavor, not of Vanilla, cream or cocoa, but Rather to me anyways,  I tasted Medio Tiempo. Something I taste usually when smoking a Cohiba BHK. Very refreshing to taste this kind of flavor in a non Cuban cigar. By 2/3 of the stick, that sweet flavor was so dominant and tasty! The last 3rd of the stick, the sweetness faded and that’s where I laid the stick to rest. If your asking me if I would pay 60 dollars to smoke this stick again? My answer is yes, I’ll skip the steak 🥩 dinner and smoke my dessert 😉 Click on the IGTV icon and rotate your phone sideways for better viewing ✌🏻
.
.
.
#bbmf #onlyfuenteisfuente #cigarworld #botl #sotl #cigarreview #whiskylicious #whistlepigsamuraiscientist

node.text: 🎅🏼Pappy X Fuente🐂 being overly priced secondary, doesn’t mean it isn’t good. Pappy 15 is my favorite of the Pappy line up 🔝 Proper drinking ABV, great flavors and finish. Not oaky at all, just well balanced. On the other hand, Opus X Taurus the Bull 🐂 💨  Awesome blend, cream and cocoa flavors. This vitola has always been a favorite of mine in the Fuente line. Age a few and these and see what I mean ☝🏼Happy hump day everyone 🐂💨

node.text:
Double take Tuesday 🎬 

Macallan XFuenteX Macallan 🦾 First time I tried this dram was in Vegas at my big bro @scotchandtime Vegas event. I had no expectations and it totally blew me away. After finding out some info, it was released in Taiwan 🇹🇼 and in Japan 🇯🇵 only, so I had to get it! Special thanks to @whiskyvegas on one of the bottles and the other one I got lucky, it purply ☔️ rained in my lap 😎 Cheers everyone and have a great day 👌🏻

node.text: It’s a Green Monday, “HULK SMASH!” 🦾 it’s been a crazy few weeks, a growing experience in Fatherhood for sure. Like the Hulk, time to smash the Virus 🦠 and get better 🦾 The Hakushu 18, one of my favorite Japanese 🇯🇵 drams 🥃 with the peat 👃🏼 done just right 👌🏻 Have a great week everyone, stay safe! 🙏🏻

node.text: Another all nighter, 4 nights in a row. We broke Archers Fever 🤒 earlier this week then Paxton had his. Watching them cough and sleep so uncomfortably really hurts. As a parent you just wanna take that pain away or take it for yourself so they don’t have to go thru it. We are in strange times def, wish all of you and your family health and happiness. Cheers 🙏🏻
